                      <item xml:id="e01">
                        <desc>
                          words of text are written interlinearly (<locus target="#12r #25v #27v #28v"/>, etc.);
                          and lines of text are written interlinearly (<locus target="#29r #32r"/>);
                          erasure markings are visible (<locus target="#26v #42rv #87v"/>, etc.);
                          text has been removed (e.g., <locus target="#27r #55v"/>).
                          There is an extensive amount of scribal
                          interaction using symbols referring to text in the top margin in at
                          least four distinct scribal hands. First is a hand writing in pencil and
                          the symbol (┴) is used (e.g.<locus target="#3v"/>, col. 2, line 3; <locus target="#4v"/>, col. 2, line 7; <locus target="#5r"/>, col. 1, line 9)
                          and later the symbol (+) is used (e.g., f<locus target="#35r"/>, col. 2, line
                          2; <locus target="#51v"/>, col. 1, line 5; <locus target="#52r"/>, col. 1, line 3).
                          Second is a hand in ink pen and
                          the symbol (+) is used (<locus target="#24v"/>, col. 1, line 11; <locus target="#26r"/>, col. 1, line 24). Third is
                          a hand in black ink and the symbol (+) is used (<locus target="#29r"/>, col. 1, line 14; <locus target="#44r"/>,
                          col. 1, line 3). Fourth is another hand in black ink and the symbols (┴
                          and +) are used (<locus target="#29r"/>, col. 2, line 18; <locus target="#30r"/>, col. 1, line 1; <locus target="#31v"/>, col. 1, line
                          9). Other instances may point to additional scribal hands (e.g., <locus target="#93v"/>,  col. 2, line 20)
                        </desc>
                      </item>
                    </list>
